Package slogo.compiler.token

Class SLogoFunction

java.lang.Object
slogo.compiler.token.SLogoToken
slogo.compiler.WorkspaceEntry
slogo.compiler.token.SLogoFunction
All Implemented Interfaces:
SLogoRunnable
Direct Known Subclasses:
SLogoUserDefinedFunction
public class SLogoFunction
extends WorkspaceEntry
implements SLogoRunnable
A Function is a Token than extends SLogoRunnable and WorkspaceEntry. Contains a collection of Token objects. This object can also be added as an entry into the Workspace. This object is runnable and can recursively call other runnable types.

    • run

      public SLogoToken run()
      Iterates through the Deque of Token objects representing the commands the user has entered, creating and running commands. The method runCommand takes care of running individual commands.
      Specified by:
      run in interface SLogoRunnable
      Returns:
      - the final command's return value in the form of a Token

    • runCommand

      private SLogoToken runCommand​(SLogoCommand command, java.util.Deque<SLogoToken> remainingTokens)
      Calls runCommand() recursively to take care of nested SLogoRunnables. If runnable.isReady() is true, call run() on the it and return the return value. If runnable is not ready, call getNextToken() and check what type of token it is. If it is type Constant or Variable, pass it to the SLogoRunnable using runnable.giveNextExpectedToken() and make check if it is ready. Constants are wrapped in a variable token for consistency in parameters. If the type is SLogoRunnable, make recursive run() call on the inner runnable, passing the return value to the outer runnable using runnable.giveNextExpectedToken().
      Returns:
      the return value of the last runnable object in the form of a Token

    • runSingleCommand

      public SLogoToken runSingleCommand()
      This method should be used when only one command should be evaluated instead of the entire Deque of tokens. This method is especially helpful with the EvaluateNumberCommand class, which is used when evaluating arguments in a parameter list.
      Returns:
      - the return value of the command in the form of a Token

    • isReady

      public boolean isReady()
      Description copied from interface: SLogoRunnable
      Indicates whether a SLogoRunnable is ready to be run based on whether it has the correct parameters. A runnable is initialized with no parameters by the Parser class, but the Function class will continuously call isReady() on each of its runnable objects and give them parameters until they are ready to be run.
      Specified by:
      isReady in interface SLogoRunnable
      Returns:
      - true if the given parameters match the expected number and type(s), false otherwise

    • giveNextExpectedToken

      public boolean giveNextExpectedToken​(SLogoToken token)
      Description copied from interface: SLogoRunnable
      Gives the runnable the next Token it expects as a parameter. For example, the fd command expects a constant or variable, so calling this method with one of those Token types will cause isReady() to return true and allow the command to be properly run. By contract, it is the Function class's responsibility to call this method with a proper Token type (i.e. by wrapping return values from a command into a Constant object).
      Specified by:
      giveNextExpectedToken in interface SLogoRunnable
      Parameters:
      token - - a Token expected by the Command as a parameter
